Auto-gen sites using Tailwind v4 (`@tailwindcss/postcss`) CANNOT use the old `@tailwind base; @tailwind components; @tailwind utilities;` directives. They fail with PostCSS transform errors.

**Correct pattern for Tailwind v4 + custom colors:**
```css
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --color-primary: #0d2137;
  --color-primary-light: #1a3a5c;
  --color-secondary: #2ecc71;
  --color-secondary-dark: #27ae60;
  --color-accent: #3498db;
  --color-background: #f8f9fa;
  --color-surface: #ffffff;
  --color-surface-muted: #f1f3f5;
  --color-foreground: #2d2d2d;
  --color-foreground-light: #6b6b6b;
  --color-foreground-muted: #9ca3af;
  --color-border: #e5e7eb;
  --font-heading: "Playfair Display", serif;
  --font-body: "Montserrat", sans-serif;
}

body {
  font-family: var(--font-body);
  color: var(--color-foreground);
  background: var(--color-background);
}
```

**Pitfall:** `@theme` generates Tailwind utility classes automatically. `--color-primary` becomes `bg-primary`, `text-primary`, `border-primary`. Old `tailwind.config.ts` with `theme.extend.colors` is NO LONGER used — the CSS `@theme` block is the single source of truth.

### Lucide Icon Validation

Not all lucide-react icon names exist. Common failures:
- `Spa` → does NOT exist. Use `Flower2` or `Spade`.
- `Dumbbell` → exists and is valid.
- `Scissors` → exists and is valid.

Always verify before committing: search `node_modules/lucide-react/dist/esm/lucide-react.mjs` or check the live build output.

### Python f-string + JSX Template Literal Conflict

When generating JSX via Python f-strings, **do NOT use backtick template literals** (`className={`${var}`}`) — the `$` + `{}` will be interpreted by Python's f-string parser, producing literal `${var}` text in the output instead of evaluating the JS expression.

**Fix:** Use string concatenation instead:
```python
# WRONG — produces literal `${var}` in output
f'<html className="${{montserrat.variable}} ${{playfair.variable}}">'

# RIGHT — evaluates as JSX
f'<html className={{montserrat.variable + " " + playfair.variable}}>'
```

Or in the written JSX:
```tsx
// After Python evaluation, this must render as:
<html lang="es" className={montserrat.variable + " " + playfair.variable}>
```

## 7. Full Site Audit Generation

After upgrading sites, create a per-repo `LEAD-AUDIT.md` with:

### Structure
1. Executive summary (score out of 100, what's done vs broken)
2. Critical bugs (P0 items, fix immediately)
3. Site-specific content todos (per-business copy, photos, data)
4. Comparison table vs established reference sites
5. 10 categories (A-J) with 30+ items each in table format
6. Effort estimate

### Categories
```
A. Infrastructure & Deployment (Docker, Traefik, CI/CD, monitoring)
B. Code Quality & TypeScript (strict mode, types, hooks, testing)
C. Design & UX (hero, services, footer, dark mode, animations, responsive)
D. Content & Copywriting (business-specific text, blog, CTAs, FAQ)
E. Pages & Features (missing routes, booking, search, maps, social)
F. Assets & Media (logos, photos, videos, OG images, PWA)
G. SEO & Structured Data (meta tags, JSON-LD, sitemap, aria)
H. Performance (fonts, caching, bundle, Core Web Vitals)
I. Analytics & Conversion (GA4, tracking, goals)
J. Legal & Compliance (cookie consent, GDPR, accessibility)
```

### Batch Generation
```python
for r in repos:
    content = "\n".join([
        "# LEAD-AUDIT: " + r,
        "## Score: 48/100",
        ...
    ])
    write_file(f"/root/{r}/LEAD-AUDIT.md", content)
```

